# Data Validation Rules

## Jakarta Bean Validation
- Use `jakarta.validation.constraints` annotations in DTOs and Entities.
- Common annotations: `@NotNull`, `@NotBlank`, `@Size`, `@Email`, `@Min`, `@Max`.

## Request Validation
- Add `@Valid` or `@Validated` to Controller method arguments (e.g., `@RequestBody @Valid CreateUserRequest request`).
- Handle `MethodArgumentNotValidException` globally in `GlobalExceptionHandler`.

## Custom Validation
- Create custom annotations for complex business rules if reusable.
- Implement `ConstraintValidator<A, T>`.

## Example
```java
public class UserDto {
    @NotBlank(message = "Name is required")
    private String name;

    @Email(message = "Invalid email format")
    private String email;
}
```
